<br>
1-4 Nektulos Forest<br>
5-12 Paludal Caverns (mushrooms and bugs)<br>
12-13 Steamfont (minotaur slavers - to regain Ak'Anon faction)<br>
14-16 Kurns Tower (bone chips for my husband!)<br>
17-20 Paludal Caverns <br>
21-24 Lake of Ill Omen (killing Explorers for knives for Cabilis faction - terrible XP though, only do if you want to annoy Iksar)<br>
25-26 Najena, getting focus items (Crystal room)<br>
27-35 Overthere (cacti and cockatrices mainly ... cats hit hard, and I wanted sarnaks to like me)<br>
36-40 Eastern Wastes (Ulthorks on the north shore are excellent money, hunters are very low on HP and SO easy to kill - also a good place for wizards to practice quad kiting)<br>
41-45 Katta Castellum (kill the guards around the zone to Tenebrous - it's safe to sit by the zone line, loads of single pulls, excellent money.  Run to Grimling Forest to sell.)<br>
45-46 Crystal Caverns (killing geonids - easy to kill, great XP, and super money if they're not camped)<br>
<br>
Since 46 I've mainly been grouped as I was finally of rank to group with my (65th rank) husband.  Katta would still be a good place to solo, the Scarlet Desert is supposed to be good also - up on the plateau, for example.  I go to Grimling Forest and fight my way into the Acrylia Caverns through the mines there - they're blue and light blue at 52, good experience, and good money to solo.<br>
<br>
From 35+ I would also recommend going to the Tenebrous Mountains and killing grimlings in the mines on the south wall - the furthest from the zone to Grimling Forest is the best mine for single pulls.  They are very good money and good experience.  And from time to time you'll see the grimling runner go by - if you get his pouch and can find someone liked in Katta who's willing to turn it in for you, you can get a Rallic Pack (75% weight reduction 10 slot bag).<br>
<br>
